The paper focuses on developing a robust network-in-the-loop control system for autonomous navigation and landing of Unmanned-Aerial-Vehicles (UAVs) using visual-inertial sensor data. This involves developing a deep neural network architecture for visual-inertial odometry, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The application of this architecture is for autonomous navigation and control of UAVs, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves simulation results for the autonomous landing of the aerial vehicle, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
